Carstens Says Mexico Needs Structural Reforms Amid World Crisis

-- B y   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 
2011-10-03T14:56:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/carstens-says-mexico-needs-structural-reforms-amid-world-crisis.html
Mexico  needs structural reforms to
face up to the problems in developed countries, central bank
Governor Agustin Carstens said at a conference in Mexico City
today.  Mexico needs the reforms “to boost domestic growth amid
the global slowdown,” Carstens said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carlos Manuel Rodriguez in Mexico City at 
 carlosmr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Richard Jarvie at 
 rjarvie@bloomberg.net  